  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650991427466-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650991427466-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650991427466-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650991427466-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1650991427466-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>red onion[s] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1715078857550-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1715078857550-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1715078857550-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1715078857550-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1715078857550-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped aubergine</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to the dish with your<strong> butternut squash cubes</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>baharat</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1715078863281-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1715078863281-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1715078863281-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1715078863281-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1715078863281-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Add your <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> and <strong>umami seasoning</strong></p><p>Add a knob of <strong>butter </strong>with a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> </strong>250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [325ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[425ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1715078866889-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1715078866889-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1715078866889-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1715078866889-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1715078866889-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Give everything a good mix up and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for an initial 30-35 min or until the sauce has thickened and the aubergine has softened – this is your <strong>oven-baked</strong> <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>aubergine tagine</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715078869860-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715078869860-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715078869860-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715078869860-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715078869860-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> white long grain rice </strong>to<strong> </strong>an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with your <strong>chopped dates</strong>, a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cover tightly with<strong> tin foil</strong>,<strong> </strong>then<strong> </strong>put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked – this is your <strong>fruity rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1715078873724-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1715078873724-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1715078873724-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1715078873724-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1715078873724-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1715078877533-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1715078877533-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1715078877533-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1715078877533-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1715078877533-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> oven-baked</strong> <strong>spiced</strong> <strong>aubergine tagine </strong>with the<strong> fruity rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Chop your<strong> parsley</strong> roughly over the top with scissors</p><p>Garnish with your <strong>flaked almonds</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
